communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please supply the full emails that are highlighted in the attached email log. The email log was supplied via FOIA #11994. This includes email control numbers FN011994-111722-1-0000000165, FN011994-111722-1-0000000166, FN011994-111722-1-0000000167 and FN011994-111722-1-0000000168.

Because this request is in the public interest for Illinois nonprofit The FOIA Bakery’s work to advocate for public education, please waive any fees in accordance with 5 ILCS § 140/6(c). Feel free to contact me with any questions, or if clarification is needed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Miriam Bhimani

communications.subject: Government Records Access and Management Act Request: Incident Report: Gang-Related Shooting 1/13/2019
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Government Records Access and Management Act, I hereby request the following records:

Incident report: gang-related shooting 
Date: Sunday, Jan. 13, 2019
Location: Fashion Place Mall, 6191 S State St, Murray, UT 84107

Individuals arrested in connection with this incident: 

Steven Perez Hernandez (Age 18 at arrest date)
Flaviano Aguilar (Age 20 at arrest date)
Jorge Luis-Crecencio-Gonzalez (Age 19 at arrest date)
Arian Huerta (Age 20 at arrest date)
Jesus Joshua Payan-Mendoza (Age 19 at arrest date)
Alexis Giovanny Gallegos (Age 17 at age of incident)

Records to be requested:
-Incident report
-Police photos
-Body cam: footage of arrest if available
-Police notes
-Video/audio of police interrogation

I am a producer with Vice News, this request is made for the purpose of news gathering and not for commercial use.
 
I request an expedited processing of this request as this information provides great value to public interest and thus is time sensitive.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jennifer Solorio
